thirstguide-text:
Survival Guide: Thirst Management
One bar wasn't enough
Guide for Balanced Thirst.

Thirst
Together with a hunger bar, you now have a thirst bar. Keep an eye on it! Its value will affect your hunger rate. If you're well hydrated, you will get hungry more slowly but the inverse is also true: when below 50%, you will get hungry faster. You can drink either from containers, or directly from the source.

Water Purity
Not all water is born equal. Normal water will have a small chance of being contaminated and making you vomit! You don't want to do so, as it will drastically lower your hydration and saturation. To avoid that, you can:
1 Boil water in a kettle (best to let it cool before drinking)
2 Look for pure spring water with a dowsing rod
3 Distill water in a boiler to obtain distilled water
Pure water has the lowest natural chance of making you vomit. Distilled water has no chance of doing so, but it will not grant any euhydration.

Water Expires
Water will get contaminated by being held in containers that aren't properly sealed, and will get progressively less pure. Carve a gourd out of a dried calabash or use other (configurable) containers to keep it clean and pure for longer. Liquid Containers is heavily suggested.

Euhydration
Euhydration is a health boost acquired thorough regular hydration. Drinking salt water or urine will lower it! Distilled water will not grant any euhydration.

Dehydration And Hot Weather
Consuming certain items, like salt water or urine will dehydrate you, increasing your thirst rate. So will do other food items (mostly alcohol and grain) but to a much lower degree. The more hydrated you are, the faster this you can recover. When temperatures get too high, sweating will increase your thirst rate. Wearing warm clothes in hot weather is discouraged as it will dehydrate you even faster.

Mod Compatibility

Rivers: River water is potable.
A Culinary Artillery: You can boil water in a cauldron or saucepan. You have to place the water in the inventory slots when on the firepit, not inside the cauldron like a container.
Hydrate or Diedrate: clothing cooling will reduce your dehydration in hot weather.
XSkills: the Camel Hump and Elephant Bladder skills will increase your capacity for the thirst and bladder bars.
